  "body": "Just a brain dump, to be taken lightly, but a list of items we should consider refactoring:\r\n\r\n* [x] Move type and structure exceptions into it's own layer. Once you get to ast->lll step you don't want to worry about types.\r\n* [x] Move external call logic from stmt.py and expr.py into it's own module.\r\n* [x] Move constant folding into it's own compilation step.\r\n* [x] Refactor arg packing functions, one implementation that works for all use cases.\r\n* [x] Check if we should consider spinning off basetype into subtypes (with their own classes).\r\n* [x] Consider breaking up parse_func some more, and moving function parsing steps into parser/functions.py\r\n* [x] Opportunity to leverage class inheritance in Vyper codebase - https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/issues/1032",
